metadata.name: haluna #114
metadata.description:
Algorithmic bit knitting.

Textural pattern studies with XOR operator.

Best experienced in fullscreen.

Probabilities;

- 4 compositions with variations.

- 7 different fixed color palettes & an algorithmic color palette generator.

- 2 different canvas aspect ratio.

In live mode, press ‘s’ to save as PNG (1500 x 2000px or 2666 x 2000px )

Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, June 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #99
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Maquette #69
metadata.description:
Like a photography of a city maquette with citizens.

Created in javascript / webGL using three.js and pathtracer.
May - June 2022
@arthurmchr

———
Path tracing is an heavy GPU operation.
Depending on the device, it can takes a few seconds to render.
Worked on Chrome and Firefox.

In live mode :
press S to export a PNG of the rendered image.
press P to pause / resume rendering (automatically paused after 100 rendering steps).

metadata.name: Wires for pride #2
metadata.description:
Rainbow wires show us a better world, with all possible bonds, crossing ideas, freedom and no discrimination.

90% 1st sales and 90% royalties will go to "#LGBTQIA+ Impact Index Fund" created by @TheGivingBlock that will match the donations for a limited time.

Press "p" to pause, press again "p" to restart.
Press "s" to save as jpg.

Generative artwork by Gandhiavelli, @gandhiavelli. Made with p5js in 2022.

metadata.name: Annihilate This Week #141
metadata.description:
This is a companion piece to "Saturday Night's Alright (For Fighting)" (project #14045). Same algorithm of the previous one, only slightly modified, the main difference is that here the daily variations are all mixed up together and the output doesn't change based on the current day.

This is intended to be a gift for all collectors and the community of fx(hash) that showed so much support for the "Saturday" project, really beyond my expectations.

50% of the royalties goes to the minter, do with the piece whatever you'd like, hold it, sell or trade it, or even burn it if you really don't like it :)

Thank you!

----

Made with p5.js
